description: Integer part of geometric mean of distinct numbers that can be formed from the nonzero digits of n.
example: a(12) = 4: the distinct numbers formed by the digits of 12 are 1, 2, 12, 21. The geometric mean of these numbers is 504^(1/4)=4.73813722053758678534150735741308... and the integer part is 4.
author: _Amarnath Murthy_, May 06 2001
